title: For Sale:  Romanian AK47 - 4 Clips, Tactical Rails, and 200 RNDs Ammo (AK-47) PRICE DROP
postcontent:
This is a Century International Arms Romanian AK47 built in 1971 with loads of extras. 

It includes the following:
-Ultimate Arms Gear Collapsible Stock
-UTG 5th Gen Quick Detach Side Mount for Optics
-UTG Pro Quad Rail
-UTG Foregrip
-Ergonomic Pistol Grip
-NCStar 3x-9x illuminated tactical scope
-4 30 Round Clips
-Roughly 200 Rounds of Ammunition

Please note, this DOES NOT come with the Vortex Sparc red dot sight as shown in the pictures, I have sold that separately. 

A lot of people have messaged me wondering how the AK-47 compares to theAR-15 so I'm going to include that here. First, the AK-47 is an unbelievablysimple gun, it's very easy to break down and clean. Second, the AK-47 is remarkably reliable, and it will shoot nearly any ammunition regardless of how horrible it is. Third, the 7.62 x 39mm ammunition that the AK-47 shoots packs significantly more punch than the AR-15's 5.56 x 45mm. Fourth, this gun is very cheap compared to the AR-15 and a lot of the accessories are more readily available even in today’s market. Now for the bad, this gun is not well known for its accuracy. With that being said accuracy for this gun is greatly impacted by the ammo being used, don't expect top accuracy if you're shooting garbage ammo. The upside is that this gun will consistently shoot cheap-o ammo whereas the AR-15 will have problems. Had I decided to not sell the gun, I would have absolutely upgraded to a chrome lined barrel with a nice compensator, and probably upgraded the bolt carrier assembly. The bottom line is, if you want decent accuracy out of an AK, shoot decent ammo.
